title: Energy spectra of neutrons produced by alpha-particles in thick targets of light elements.

x4freetext: NE213 liquid scintillator of 5 cm diam. and
The uncertainties for the spectral values have been
derived by taking into account the uncertainties of
target stability and charge measurement (+- 2.0%), of
neutron detection efficiency (+-3.2 to 5.2%)and of the
contribution due to statistics and neutron energy
determination varies strongly with the neutron energy
interval considered. The rather strong correlations
among the detector efficiencies for different neutron
energies have been taken into account.
Measurements have been made for following materials:
C,Mg,Al,Si,BN,CaF2,Al2O3,SiO2 and Uo2. In all cases
the target thickness was sufficient to stop 5.5 MeV
alpha-particles. The use of the compounds allowed the
determination of spectra for B, F and O.

The spectra for B,O and F were obtained by multiplying
the intensities of BN, UO2 and CaF2, respectively.
